revision.text:
[[File:Yakuou-ji-temple-main-chiba-feb21-2016.jpg|thumb|Main Hall]] '''Yakuō-ji''' (薬王寺) is a {{ill|Tendai|ja|天台宗|12=draft|12=draft}} Buddhist temple located in {{ill|Shiroi, Chiba|ja|白井市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Chiba Prefecture|ja|千葉県|12=draft|12=draft}}, in the {{ill|Kiyodo|ja|清戸|12=draft|12=draft}} area. The temple’s mountain name (''sangō'') is Seiryūzan, and its principal deity is {{ill|Amida Nyorai|ja|阿弥陀如来|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== History == The exact date of Yakuō-ji’s founding is unknown, but according to tradition, it was established during the {{ill|Daidō|ja|大同 (日本)|12=draft|12=draft}} era (806–810 CE). Nearby, there is a shrine dedicated to {{ill|Benzaiten|ja|弁財天 (白井市)|12=draft|12=draft}}.
[[File:Yakuou-ji-temple-yakushi-chiba-feb21-2016.jpg|thumb|Yakushi Hall]]
== Structures == * '''Main Hall''' Believed to have originally been constructed during the Daidō era. The current structure was rebuilt in 2001. * '''Yakushi Hall''' Dedicated to {{ill|Yakushi Nyorai|ja|薬師如来|1=Bhaisajyaguru|lt=Yakushi Nyorai (Me)dicine Buddha|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Cultural Properties == * '''Chiba Prefecture Designated Historic Site''' '''Kiyodo no Izumi with Woodblocks''' The woodblocks, which are related to the origin story of the {{ill|Benzaiten Shrine|ja|弁財天 (白井市)|12=draft|12=draft}} enshrined at "Kiyodo no Izumi," are preserved at this temple. "Kiyodo no Izumi" itself is located within the grounds of the {{ill|Funabashi Country Club|ja|船橋カントリークラブ|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Location == * 6 Kiyodo, Shiroi, Chiba Prefecture
{{commonscat|Yakuoji (Chiba)|Yakuō-ji}}
== External Links == * [http://www.kanko.chuo.chiba.jp/select/mokuteki/resource/s_siro_yakuo.html Yakuō-ji (Chiba Prefecture Tourism Guide)] * [http://city.shiroi.chiba.jp/webapps/www/service/detail.jsp?id=682 Shiroi City Cultural Properties]
{{buddhism-stub}} {{citation needed|Yakuō-ji (Shiroi)}} {{citation needed|Yakuō-ji (Shiroi)}} {{citation needed|Yakuō-ji (Shiroi)}}
